Author: Michael W. Burnett [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5126-5568>)
Maintainer: Michael W. Burnett <mburnett@ucsb.edu>
Description: Models for up-scaling sap flux density measurements to whole-tree
    volumetric sap flow rates using classic circular tree trunk theory or the
    new theory proposed by Burnett et al. (2026) in AgForMet for irregularly
    shaped tree trunks (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.agrformet.2026.111357).
    For questions, contact mburnett@ucsb.edu or
    mikeburnett@ucdavis.edu.
